<item>
            <title>[LU-5123] lprocfs_write_frac_u64_helper does not respect multiplier</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5123</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4856&quot; title=&quot;osc_lru_reserve()) ASSERTION( atomic_read(cli-&amp;gt;cl_lru_left) &amp;gt;= 0 ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4856&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4856&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I have made use of lprocfs_write_frac_u64_helper, which turns out to not work.  Specifically, the mult arg is ignored because of this logic:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        units = 1;&lt;br/&gt;
        if (units)&lt;br/&gt;
                mult = mult &amp;lt; 0 ? -units : units;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This led to sanity 101a setting the 64 bit converted max_cached_mb to 32 pages (not mb) - which hung in a way that may be interesting in it&apos;s own right.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
